http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 8 Mar 2019
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2019 32(11) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=29780


Equid herpesvirus-1 (EHV-1) (Infection with), Norway
----------------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 08 Mar /2019 from Dre Kristina Landsverk, Chief Veterinary Officer, Norwegian Food Safety Authority, Norwegian Food Safety Authority, Brumunddal, Norway

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 25 Feb 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 27 Feb 2019
Report date: 8 Mar 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 8 Mar 2019
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2006
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Equid herpesvirus-1 [EHV-1]
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Bergen, Flesland, Bergen Area Department, Southern and Western region, Hordaland
Date of start of the outbreak: 25 Feb 2019
Outbreak status: continuing ( or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: other
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 80 / 8 / 1 / - / - /

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages], expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 10 / 1.25 / 12.5 / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: one of the horses with herpesvirus detected participated in the Norwegian Horse Festival, Lillestrom, in February this year [2019].

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Laboklin (foreign laboratory) / Equine / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 27 Feb 2019 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This immediate notification complements the information already covered in ProMED-mail posting 20190305.6349117.

Until 2014, the disease was reported to the OIE as equine rhinopneumonitis, but since then, it is reported as equid herpesvirus-1 (EHV-1). - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Norway: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6359733,32342]
